Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.08,0:01:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In November 1942, Guadalcanal, which is said to be the most tragic battle in the Pacific Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.46,0:01:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,could not be approached by the Japanese rescue forces due to the complete control of the sea and air by the US military.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.58,0:01:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The 30,000 Japanese soldiers left on Guadalcanal Island
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.83,0:02:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,became an island of hunger, malaria, and death. And were just waiting for help
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.44,0:02:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For the Japanese side, only covert transportation by submarines was allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.78,0:02:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, as a desperate measure, the transportation of supply drums by a high-speed destroyer was devised.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan was to connect drums filled with food and medicine with ropes, approach the coast, and drop them into the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.71,0:02:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Tassafarunga (Episode 19)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.36,0:03:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On November 28th, the flagship Nagagami was moored in the hometown of Shortland, ahead of its departure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.74,0:03:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In the officer's office a final meeting was held for the commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.77,0:03:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Major General Tanaka Raizo, and the captains of the eight destroyers that were organized.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A local staff member also attended from the Imperial Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.92,0:03:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The total number of drums is 1098.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.87,0:03:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,250 of these will be placed on each of the five ships:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.85,0:03:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oyashio, Kuroshio, Kawakaze, Suzukaze, and Kagero,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.33,0:03:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,excluding the guard ship, Takanami, the flagship: Naganami, and Makinami.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.94,0:03:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine, but as I've seen, torpedoes and cannons are covered by the drums, so they can't be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Any fighting will be done by the guard ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.32,0:03:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, drop the drums safely, and then have the crews show the results of their daily training.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.43,0:03:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a express company. The non-commissioned officer said as much this morning as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.65,0:03:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,After training so much under Tanaka,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they were called the Devil's 2nd Destroyer Squadron, and then, was it a express company?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:03:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't just your saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.97,0:04:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the Guadalcanal soldiers can't eat half of this bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.58,0:04:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it is 300 nautical miles from Shortland to Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.62,0:04:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't make it to the halfway point, 150 nautical miles, before dawn,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.16,0:04:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy will chase us from their base on Guadalcanal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.30,0:04:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to finish dropping the drums at Guadalcanal by 24:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.68,0:04:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask that much. I'll' leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.70,0:04:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it staff officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the plan so far, it seems that we will not meet the enemy at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean, they may come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to ask about the strategy for that case.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.64,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.65,0:05:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.65,0:05:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems irresponsible to not plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When you walk, do you command your feet to "put out with your right foot, put out with your left foot"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.16,0:05:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like my metaphor with the legs, let's change the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the master of kendo command his hand to block when the enemy's sword arrives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.33,0:05:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't your hand going there at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether to fight well or not. It depends on daily training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.08,0:05:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why the 2nd Destroyer Squadron has trained ridiculously hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.41,0:05:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They are more than just express company. Look and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.46,0:05:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Master of the voyage. Is the chart reliable?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. It was made in England 15 years ago. It may be a little different.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.59,0:06:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's a little different? Are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be clear if I can see the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if we get on the boat, I'll leave it to you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.98,0:06:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you leave it to me, yesterday's exchange of opinions between Commander Tanaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.97,0:06:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Chief of Staff of the Imperial Headquarters was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The imperial officer who doesn't know the local area is like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Master of the voyage. The sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.67,0:06:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see it? Let's get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.40,0:06:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.97,0:06:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,1203
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.78,0:06:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,After all it was a little different. I will make a transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.01,0:06:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Outbound 175 degrees. Full starboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.68,0:07:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the enemy to come early.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.98,0:07:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy aircraft spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.40,0:07:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,331 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears to be one B-17 bomber.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.28,0:07:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare for anti-aircraft combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.05,0:07:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, anti-aircraft combat, man your station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It saw us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.28,0:08:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.24,0:08:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At the time, on the American side, the Japanese rescue fleet was called the "Tokyo express",
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.23,0:08:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was to be attacked and sunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.58,0:08:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A fleet was sent to attack them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, a fleet of 11 ships centered on the heavy cruiser Minneapolis, led by Major General Carlton Wright,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.19,0:08:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They were to wait for and find the enemy fleet intercepting the supply drums for Guadalcanal Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,As mentioned, there are eight enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.61,0:08:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's learn from the Battle of Tsushima, which was led by Admiral Togo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.90,0:08:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the enemy is best at night battles,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.15,0:08:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the water vapor of the cruiser illuminates it with tracer ammunition and destroys it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's "a rat in a trap".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.78,0:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a Japanese proverb, "a cornered rat will bite a cat". Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the enemy is the 2nd Destroyer Squadron, which has been training hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though it is a Destroyer Squadron, I don't know what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.27,0:09:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have radar. Japan has nothing like that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.07,0:09:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They rely on their eyes even when the battle is at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.77,0:09:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As you all know, in naval battles it is better to know the position of the enemy first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.04,0:09:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the Japanese side also changed course, and approached four nautical miles west of Savo Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.53,0:09:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and decided to enter Guadalcanal Island at a 180 degrees course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.66,0:10:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What time is it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,22:00
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.03,0:10:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,2 hours left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.60,0:10:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that the enemy will not find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.68,0:10:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir. From 8th Fleet Command.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.64,0:10:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.98,0:10:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,According to interceptions, the path of your fleet has been discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.25,0:10:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to destroy the enemy without sticking to your supply mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. If I meet the enemy, throw away the drums and fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.06,0:10:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.95,0:10:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Please let everyone know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes {Seems like there should be something after this yes}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.60,0:10:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope they don't find us until we drop the supplies. The soldiers on the island are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, well run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.70,0:10:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It is better to sink the enemy than to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.22,0:10:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We are an express company today. The soldiers waiting on the island are priority customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Customer first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.64,0:11:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They have made a quick escape. Can't you find the Japanese yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.69,0:11:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We need a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.73,0:11:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They know that 24 o'clock is their time limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If they are in a rush, they will definitely come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,God is smiling at us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.74,0:11:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In this rain cloud, the visibility in Japan is at most 4000m.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We have radar. We can see out to 24000m. The difference: 20000m, which can control the battle ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.72,0:11:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly there is a flagship, but at 6300m. The enemy is eight nautical miles from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.68,0:11:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, get ready for battle. Man your stations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.73,0:11:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight. All of them will be attacked and all of them will be finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.74,0:12:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Another breath. We can see the island soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.54,0:12:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy didn't notice us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.17,0:12:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we have been caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't know from where they will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.78,0:12:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's a fight between blindness and eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.07,0:12:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's just prepare to drop the supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.13,0:12:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare to drop, tell each soldier.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tanaka fleet approached the island knowing that it was being seen by the American radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.66,0:12:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It was 23:16.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.03,0:13:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,45 degrees to the left. Two black shapes. It seems to be an enemy destroyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.13,0:13:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. This has opened our dark eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.50,0:13:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How far is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,6000m!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.46,0:13:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.16,0:13:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Report to flagship. Simultaneous torpedo attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.02,0:13:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Master of the voyage. Mark it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.94,0:13:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven ships that seem to be enemy destroyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.06,0:13:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Direction 45 degrees to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.18,0:13:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy speed is 24 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.48,0:13:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.70,0:13:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all set. I'll leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you proceed without breaking formation?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.52,0:13:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, its like standing naked in front of the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.80,0:13:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. However, the mission is transportation first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.84,0:13:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be a waste to throw away supplies as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.31,0:13:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It is our mission to sink as many enemies as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.58,0:13:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We will do that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.86,0:13:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But now it's transportation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Moreover, the enemy is in front of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.57,0:14:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do as much as we can. We can see the island. They are signaling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.06,0:14:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese Navy, approach here a little more. {One sentence here, but seems like two voices? Missing line I think.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.93,0:14:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 11 enemies in all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.43,0:14:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. Do you wanna have a drink with the usual one?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.16,0:14:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm standing this time. Until we deliver the supplies to our customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.04,0:14:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I shoot? Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.53,0:14:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Wait. A little more.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.71,0:15:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese side hasn't noticed us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.68,0:15:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The first ship is showing their side. Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.47,0:15:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Pull them all in and then annihilate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay if they come over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But look. They are surrounded by enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.03,0:15:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Do they not notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.01,0:15:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.14,0:15:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot. They can never hear your yelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.53,0:15:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They are becoming prey for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.26,0:15:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.54,0:15:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still a commander?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.14,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle is an opportunity. Did you forget about such a rudimentary thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff officer, stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.66,0:15:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They are attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.97,0:15:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn the rudder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.18,0:16:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander. It's time to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.69,0:16:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Staff officer. It's me who will make the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.86,0:16:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.09,0:16:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Simultaneous fire. First of all, target the first ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.29,0:16:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it done?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.60,0:16:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Commander. Look at that. Takanami is being attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.54,0:17:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, what are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.67,0:17:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! {Lot of voices here, seems like there are missing lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.02,0:18:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The food has been dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.48,0:18:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, tell all ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge the enemy force!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.44,0:18:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Begin fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. Not yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.44,0:18:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.23,0:18:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.60,0:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Set for 3 meters deep. Third ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.04,0:18:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The pillar of fire is too much and cannot be seen well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.46,0:18:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright. The one you just shot. Again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.40,0:18:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see the face of the enemy well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.32,0:18:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Launch concentrated attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.65,0:19:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The torpedoes of the trained 2nd Destroyer Squadron on the Japanese side were powerful and accurate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.20,0:19:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One or more hits were recorded on all cruisers except Honolulu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.54,0:19:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,One heavy cruiser was sunk and three were damaged on the American side. {Original: Hits with one or more torpedoes on all cruisers except Honolulu sank one heavy cruiser and damaged three destroyers on the American side.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.73,0:20:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They used to load their luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,They will do it properly without being ordered, Staff officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain. We have to save Takanami.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.94,0:20:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was hard work, but Oyashio and Kuroshio have already defeated much of the enemy. Please go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.87,0:20:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I will tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.72,0:20:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It has became quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We won.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is almost annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.72,0:20:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. Did We win?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.93,0:20:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What was our damage?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.90,0:20:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Takanami
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.15,0:20:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That is good
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.58,0:21:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief surgeon. Now, the Oyashio and Kuroshio are coming to the rescue with the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.74,0:21:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for that. I can't handle it anymore. I usually play, so I got a punishment. {???}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.12,0:21:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, do you know where the captain is?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.57,0:21:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Near the voyage chief's room. He's sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.78,0:21:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.58,0:21:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to have a toast with the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.86,0:21:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.04,0:21:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel relaxed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.29,0:22:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE {Start of some song here, HA does not have it labeled}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.38,0:22:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.98,0:23:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.73,0:23:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.15,0:23:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry that I said something insubordinate.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.04,0:23:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand what you mean, "No one will command his right and left feet to walk.”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.03,0:23:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope Takanami can be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.67,0:23:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the night battle off Lunga was over in just 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.03,0:23:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is said that General Nimitz instructed all Navy officers to "train, train, and further train"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.57,0:23:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,after the activities and results of the Japanese destroyer fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A strategy that trusts the power of subordinates obtained from rigorous training
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.60,0:23:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and leaves everything to them with peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.26,0:23:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What is highly evaluated may be the commander's human decision.
